Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture_(1950s)	In addition to being the only Best Picture winner to date financed entirely outside of the US or UK , The Artist was the first silent winner of a Best Picture or equivalent award since Wings and Sunrise , although a part-silent version of All Quiet on the Western Front was created for foreign-language release and survives .	The Academy Award for Best Picture is one of the Academy Awards .	0







